race.comment: LEONCHROI (10) is the one with upside that can challenge. Two runs back have just been fair but he looked talented in his maiden campaign and getting to 2000m will be far more suitable. KENTUCKY NICK (4) was outclassed in a tougher race at Flemington last time and did win his only go around here. He can roll forward from the wide gate and take catching. BLACK PEPPERMINT (3) wasn't bad fresh over a mile at Flemington and will be fitter. Up in trip suits, he'll be strong late. WHAT A CROSS (7) ran in the middle of the pack last start at Warrnambool on a soft track. Is up in journey today and is a each way chance.
